  <div xmlns:v="http://rdf.data-vocabulary.org/#" typeof="v:Review">
    <div class="main review-item" id="1776622">
        

  <header class="main-hd">
    <h3 class="title">
      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/1776622/" class="title-link">要读这本书，即使不为学易</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-1776622"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/3649124/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u3649124-14.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/3649124/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">弓</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar50 main-title-rating" title="力荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2009-03-02"
      class="main-meta">2009-03-02 21:51:41</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_1776622_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                   这本书和现在比较流行的张老师、南老师等“老师”或“大师”出版的易书有很大不同，开篇就直截了当地表达了作者的一大重要观点：“易”是建立在有神论基础上的。全书对六十四卦的哲学阐述也是从有神论的角度进行的。我当然没有资格去评述作者的角度是对是错，我只是想告诉大家...

                    <a class="pl" href="https://book.douban.com/review/1776622/#comments">(1回应)</a>
                  <div class="more-info pl clearfix">
